Project 1 Submission README

Submitted files:

questions-1-10/01-system-calls-mycompress/MyCompress.c
Compresses runs of bits from an input file using Unix file system calls and writes the encoded output file.

questions-1-10/02-decompress-mydecompress/MyDecompress.c
Decompresses the +N+ and -N- encoded bit runs back into the original bit file format.

questions-1-10/03-fork-compress/ForkCompress.c
Forks a child process and uses execl to run MyCompress, then waits for the compression process to finish.

questions-1-10/04-pipe-compress/PipeCompress.c
Uses two forked processes connected by a pipe so one reads the source file while the other compresses and writes the destination file.

questions-1-10/05-parallel-fork/ParFork.c
Compresses a large input file by splitting it into chunks and using forked child processes to do the work.

questions-1-10/06-mini-shell/MiniShell.c
Implements a very small shell that runs simple commands without arguments by using fork and execlp.

questions-1-10/07-more-shell/MoreShell.c
Extends the mini shell so commands can include arguments and can be executed with execvp.

questions-1-10/08-dup-shell/DupShell.c
Adds one pipe between two commands and uses dup2 to redirect standard input and output.

questions-1-10/09-parallel-thread/ParThread.c
Compresses a large input file with pthreads by splitting the file into chunks and merging the thread results.

questions-1-10/10-timing-comparison/run_times.sh
Runs the sequential, forked process, and pthread compression programs on the same large input file so their times can be compared.

Makefile
Builds all project source files into the required executable program names.

test-runs/typescript
Placeholder for the final terminal typescript showing correct input tests and graceful error tests.

